main event: Two bright bluish white lights were observed near Cincinnati, Ohio on January 23, 1968. The lights had the ability to hover and move at extreme speeds.
interesting points: The lights were seen by two civilian witnesses for about 30 minutes.
A ground search and KC-135 aircraft in the area during the sighting did not find anything unusual.
The lights were described as hovering and then disappearing to the southeast.
The sighting was initially reported as a probable aircraft, but was later reported as an unexplained UFO sighting.
The report indicates the lights were seen in the general location of Cincinnati AFB, but the tower and ground control approach (GCA) did not see anything.
photographs: no, the report does not include any photographs
